<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="519" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1542,2035]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1542,1567]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Yellow species; sternite 
<number box="[560,574,1543,1567]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="8.0">8</number>
undivided (
<figureCitation box="[713,798,1542,1567]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[767,798,1543,1567]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="83.0">83</number>
</figureCitation>
); phallus subcylindrical, narrower apically, with ventral subapical narrow appendix (
<figureCitation box="[468,549,1578,1603]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[520,549,1579,1603]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="88.0">88</number>
</figureCitation>
) and subapical expansion laterally, more conspicuous ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[1274,1358,1578,1603]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[1326,1358,1579,1603]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="89.0">89</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="521" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1542,2035]" lastBlockId="19.[151,1436,151,608]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="521" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1614,1639]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[352,413,1614,1639]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[429,514,1614,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[482,514,1615,1639]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="80.0">80</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[533,597,1614,1639]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">Head</emphasis>
: Face with sides slightly diverging toward the proboscis, brown with gray pruinescence visible in ventral view, about 
<date box="[643,677,1651,1675]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
<number box="[643,657,1651,1675]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="4.0">4</number>
X
</date>
longer than lower width. Ocellar tubercle protuberant, brown with brown pruinescence; ocelli yellow. Antenna yellow with black bristles; postpedicel about 
<number box="[1153,1187,1686,1711]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X longer than pedicel; stylus about 
<date box="[298,332,1723,1747]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
<number box="[298,311,1723,1747]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
longer than postpedicel. Proboscis yellow shorter than head height. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1123,1212,1722,1747]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">Thorax</emphasis>
yellow, shiny (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,183,1759,1783]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="80.0">80</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs yellow, except for hind femur with black apical ring and all tarsomeres 
<number box="[1072,1114,1758,1783]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
brown, hind tibia and tarsus with anterodorsal and posterodorsal rows of longer bristles. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[826,891,1794,1819]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">Wing</emphasis>
hyaline, pterostigma brown, conspicuous, about 
<number box="[151,186,1831,1855]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="2.2">2.2</number>
X longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[428,514,1830,1855]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[483,514,1831,1855]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="81.0">81</number>
</figureCitation>
). Halter yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[708,825,1830,1855]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">Abdomen</emphasis>
yellow, shiny (
<figureCitation box="[1004,1141,1830,1855]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">Figs 80, 82</figureCitation>
); tergite 
<number box="[1245,1259,1831,1855]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="8.0">8</number>
divided in two subrectangular plates; sternite 
<number box="[492,506,1867,1891]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="8.0">8</number>
undivided (
<figureCitation box="[641,724,1866,1891]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[693,724,1867,1891]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="83.0">83</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[744,875,1866,1891]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">Terminalia</emphasis>
: Anterior cercus with proclinate dorsal projection in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[342,483,1902,1927]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">Figs 82, 84</figureCitation>
), posterior margin with median sinus in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1129,1218,1902,1927]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[1187,1218,1902,1927]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="85.0">85</number>
</figureCitation>
); descendant plate subrectangular and lower margin slightly convex in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[913,997,1938,1963]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[965,997,1938,1963]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="86.0">86</number>
</figureCitation>
). Posterior cercus with acuminate apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[328,460,1974,1999]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">Figs 82, 84</figureCitation>
); without dorsal projections (
<figureCitation box="[790,874,1974,1999]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[843,874,1974,1999]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="85.0">85</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypoproct rounded in lateral view and covering mesially the posterior cercus in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[712,796,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[764,796,2011,2035]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrial ventral lobe rounded at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1266,1349,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[1318,1349,2011,2035]" pageId="17" pageNumber="519" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
), with spiniform bristles mesially and longer bristles apically. Hypandrium wider than long, with concave apex (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1423,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 89" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox="[158,1434,193,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[152,1435,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 89. Opeatocerata cylindrophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 80. habitus, lateral view; 81. wing apex; 82. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 83. sternite 8, ventral view; 84. terminalia, lateral view; 85. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 86. descendant plate of anterior cercus, posterior view; 87. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 88. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 89. phallus and hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252530/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="521">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1423,152,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="521" value="89.0">89</number>
</figureCitation>
), without long bristles. Phallus subcylindrical, narrower apically, longer than hypandrium, with ventral subapical narrow appendix (
